This paper focuses on evaluating the quality of word embeddings of identifiers in source code, which is a key aspect of software engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). However, the paper also discusses various embedding techniques and evaluates their effectiveness, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Hence, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper involves surveying software developers and analyzing their responses, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
